Will each “world” be a mirror image of each other?<br>
<br>
No.  In Shadowbane, all of our worlds (gaming environments) are completely unique. When the Turning occurred, Aerynth was literally torn asunder, broken into an array of fragments great and small. Each “world” or “server-cluster” in Shadowbane is one of these fragments, a portion of the original world. Rather than the identical &quot;mirrored&quot; worlds presented by other games in the current market, Shadowbane will consist of many interlinked &quot;world fragments&quot; scattered throughout a universe, each with their own unique feel and flavor. One fragment might be almost entirely jungle, while another could consist of frigid Arctic regions. Imagine the different worlds that might result if the Earth were to shatter, and you'll get the idea. Unlike most other online games, individual characters will be able to travel between world fragments through magical gates and portals. The traditional model of distinct, discrete &quot;servers&quot; will not exist in Shadowbane. <br>
<br>
<br>
2.08  Are there &quot;zones&quot;? <br>
<br>
No, not in the traditional sense: the landscape of each “world” is seamless. We may refer to various areas as a “zone”, like a Desert Zone or an Elven Ruin Zone, but there is no “Stop and Load” time associated with moving between them. Instead, the world is constantly loading around you as your character moves, keeping a preset circumference of terrain loaded around you at all times.  Further, this area is larger than your character can “see” - so there won't be blind spots as you travel around the world. <br>
<br>
