<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> What happens if the defending Guild Leader is killed during a Siege?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
He comes back, winded, and possibly with fewer of his items, just like any other character.  Bear in mind, however, that a Guild Leader comes back from death &quot;enshrouded&quot; by the Shadow Beyond. As long as the Guild Leader is enshrouded, he or she cannot adjust the powers of the Tree of Life. The distribution of a Tree's healing energies will stay however the Guild Leader last set them, until the effect wears off. Attackers can then shift their attack to structures without any healing, destroying them before the defenders can adjust their defensive tactics. <br>
<br>
